                            <comment id="12761225" author="fyrewyld" created="Thu, 1 Oct 2009 15:17:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed fix, patch for the 1.2.x stream&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12776834" author="ppoddar@apache.org" created="Thu, 12 Nov 2009 04:40:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ClassMetaData is not the right place for holding cache information, imo.&lt;br/&gt;
Firstly, for practical use cases, caches are hardly partitioned by types. &lt;br/&gt;
Secondly, the cache eligibility logic may be more user configurable than assigning all instances of a type statically to a single named cache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DataCacheManager seems to be much better abstraction to implement cache assignment to instances (even if only based on types).&lt;br/&gt;
These changes are incorporated in trunk for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1334&quot; title=&quot;Support instance level distribution policy for named cache partitions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;OPENJPA-1334&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;OPENJPA-1334&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
